parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Corrosion of Fuel Tank Straps and Mounting Brackets
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of fuel tank straps and mounting brackets can cause the fuel tank to detach from the vehicle, leading to fuel leaks, fires, and accidents.
symptoms: Fuel tank straps and mounting brackets are corroded
or broken; fuel tank is loose or detached from the vehicle; fuel leaks or spills; strong fuel odor.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure of Fuel Tank and Fuel Tank Straps
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel tank and fuel tank straps can cause fuel leaks, fires, and accidents.
symptoms: Fuel tank is fractured or ruptured; fuel tank straps are broken or corroded; fuel leaks or spills; strong fuel odor.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Inadequate Repair of Fuel Tank Straps under Recall
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inadequate repair of fuel tank straps under recall can lead to continued fuel leaks, fires, and accidents.
symptoms: Fuel tank straps are not properly replaced or repaired under recall; fuel leaks or spills; strong fuel odor; corrosion of fuel tank straps and mounting brackets.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The ejection of a spark plug can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing an accident. Additionally, the spark plug can ignite fuel vapors, resulting in a fire.
symptoms: Spark plug blows out of the cylinder head
fuel vapors leaking into the engine compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Coolant leaks can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing an engine failure, which can lead to accidents.
Exhaust header bolt failure can cause exhaust leaks, which can lead to carbon monoxide poisoning and potentially cause a fire.
symptoms: rusted or broken exhaust header bolts

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine fires can cause serious damage to the vehicle and potentially harm occupants.
symptoms: flames coming from the engine compartment
smoke and fumes in the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden tire tread separation can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
Valve stem failure can cause sudden loss of air pressure, leading to accidents and injuries.
Spare tire cable failure can cause the spare tire to fall off the vehicle, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Spare tire falls off the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch master cylinder failure can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
